                            =============
                            README-jabber
                            =============


This brief text describes the jabber features supported:

  * Ordinary messages, one-to-one chat, and groupchat.

  * Disco.

  * Groupchat is supported via the "old" 'groupchat 1.0' protocol,
    via the never approved, but wide spread, jabber:iq:conference method,
    and MUC.

  * File transfer using the oob method (http actually).

  * Handles forms using jabber:x:data

  * The Coccinella client can be discoed to, and returns the following
    namespace declarations describing its services:

      o jabber:client
      o jabber:iq:browse
      o jabber:iq:last
      o jabber:iq:oob
      o jabber:iq:roster
      o jabber:iq:time
      o jabber:iq:version
      o jabber:x:data
      o jabber:x:event
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/bytestreams 
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/disco 
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/disco#items
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/disco#info
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/ibb 
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/muc 
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/si 
      o http://jabber.org/protocol/si/profile/file-transfer
      o http://coccinella.sourceforge.net/protocol/servers
      o http://coccinella.sourceforge.net/protocol/whiteboard
   

Note, however, that the jabber protocols outside the very core, are a moving 
target, and that changes and adoptions takes place at a rapid pace.
